Chelsea, Manchester City Compete to Sign Real Madrid’s Kaka, Mirror Says

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-03-13T12:46:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-13/chelsea-manchester-city-compete-to-sign-real-madrid-s-kaka-mirror-says.html
Chelsea and  Manchester City  will
compete at the end of the season to sign Real Madrid’s Brazil
playmaker Kaka, the  Sunday Mirror reported , without saying where
it got the information.  Madrid wants about 40 million pounds ($64 million) for the
28-year-old, who joined the Spanish soccer club in June 2009 for
56 million pounds, the newspaper said.  Chelsea is confident that Kaka will snub City to join the
Blues, linking up with coach  Carlo Ancelotti  who worked with the
player at AC Milan, the Mirror reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  